SIMPLE: lively
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lively
<hw>Live"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Livelier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Liveliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[For <ets>lifely</ets>. Cf.
<er>Lifelike</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Endowed with or manifesting
life; living.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Chaplets of gold and silver resembling <qex>lively</qex> flowers
and leaves.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Brisk; vivacious; active; <as>as, a <ex>lively</ex>
youth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But wherefore comes old Manoa in such haste,⟦br⟧
With youthful steps ? Much <qex>livelier</qex> than erewhile⟦br⟧
He seems.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Gay; airy; animated; spirited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From grave to gay, from <qex>lively</qex> to severe.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Representing life; lifelike.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I spied the <qex>lively</qex> picture of my father.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Bright; vivid; glowing; strong; vigorous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The colors of the prism are manifestly more full, intense, and
<qex>lively</qex> that those of natural bodies.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I.
Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His faith must be not only living, but <qex>lively</qex> too.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lively stones</b></col> <fld>(Script.)</fld>, <cd>saints,
as being quickened by the Spirit, and active in holiness.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Brisk; vigorous; quick; nimble; smart; active;
alert; sprightly; animated; spirited; prompt; earnest; strong;
energetic; vivid; vivacious; blithe; gleeful; airy; gay;
jocund.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lively</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lively
<hw>Live"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a brisk, active,
or animated manner; briskly; vigorously.</def>
<rj><au>Hayward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With strong resemblance of life.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou counterfeitest most <qex>lively</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>liven</ent>⟦br⟧
